My parents told me not to lick the Hist tree until my Naming Day, so I did.
My parents caught me and a boy from my nest in a soft-leaf patch right before the naming ceremony.
I feared I'd get more of a licking from my parents than I gave the tree...
So I ran as fast as I could through the swamp and into the rest of the kids waiting for their naming ceremony.
Everyone had a good laugh and the name stuck.
